HEADWORD: Buttonbush
<hw>But"ton*bush`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A shrub (<spn>Cephalanthus occidentalis</spn>) growing by the
waterside; -- so called from its globular head of flowers. See
<er>Capitulum</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>buttoned</ent>⟦br⟧
